work.title: Kvintet for to violiner, to bratscher og cello
Quintet for Two Violins, Two Violas and Cello

contributor.persName: Thorvald Nielsen-Kvartetten (Thorvald Nielsen, Erling Bloch, Hans Kassow, Louis Jensen), 1931

history.p: After having established his reputation as a young, talented and promising composer in 1888, Nielsen started composing the quintet for strings. The last three movements were apparently completed between October 1888 and January 1889. According to Emilie Demant Hatt's manuscript, Foraarsbølger, the quintet was completed on 1 January 1889.

annot.p: Published in: John Fellow (ed.): Emilie Demant Hatt, Foraarsbølger, Copenhagen 2002. The quintet is mentioned on p. 92.
